ric risk score and the risk model's fraud probability, so the reviewer can see which model flagged the transaction and why.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is output contract assembly across modules (score output + risk probability + flag provenance). Unit-level formatter tests can miss dropped/mis-mapped fields introduced in service/DTO wiring. Higher levels were rejected: no real OS/network/subprocess required, and no dependence on real AI decision quality for this contract check.","test_description":"Run the transaction evaluation pipeline with deterministic model outputs and validate the produced response DTO/API payload contains numeric score, fraud probability, and per-model flag metadata with correct field names/types/values.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.28,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
